```json
{
  "application": "spack",
  "software": [
    "meson@0.60.0",
    "gcc@10.2.0",
    "python@3.8.12",
    "openjdk@11.0.12_7.sh"
  ],
  "resources": {
    "scheduler": "slurm",
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks_per_node": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 10,
    "memory": "93G",
    "gpus": 1,
    "time": "00:30:00"
  }
}
```

This script is running the `spack` package manager to install `meson@0.60.0` with the `gcc@10.2.0` compiler and its dependencies. It utilizes the `slurm` scheduler and requires a single node with 1 task per node, 10 cpus per task, 93GB of memory, 1 GPU, and a maximum runtime of 30 minutes. The script also includes a `openjdk@11.0.12_7.sh` script that is scheduled to run after the installation finishes.
